Undid revision 1041131390 by [[Special:Contributions/Ch.AhmedRaza23|Ch.AhmedRaza23]] ([[User talk:Ch.AhmedRaza23|talk]]): please stop.

The claim "It is not Halal for Muslims" and the reference to the Qur'anic verse for pigs is invalid. There is no ayat in the Qur'an about E631, especially as E631 can be made from various sources. Secondly, there is a huge science behind what you can call Halal and Haram; for example, in Islamic Fiqh the quantity of impurity plays a factor, due to which many scholars deem Cheese to be halal despite the presence of animal rennet. And this sentence really felt out-of-place anyway.
